        "message": "LU-3067 osc: use o_handle even it used in brw_interpret\n\nin brw_interpret, the ldlm lock handle used by reada needs to be\ncanceled after reada completes, but the \"o_handle\" in obdo could\nalready be used to contain the lock handle to prolong at OST, and\nit won't be used anymore after reply is received, then \"o_handle\"\ncan be used in these two cases.\n\nChange-Id: Ic1cc45db1e12414e0393dcdb166b80422ba9029b\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@intel.com>\n"
